cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.PL. 

The paper proposes a tool for software developers that analyzes an encountered exception and its context in the IDE, and recommends relevant web pages for the exception. This involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) to provide a better user experience. The tool is also related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) as it aims to assist developers in debugging their code. Additionally, the tool has implications for cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) as it can help developers find solutions to security vulnerabilities in their code.
